This query retrieves:
	• The SQL Server instance name.
	• The total number of databases.
	• The number of databases that are online.
	• The number of databases that allow multiple users.
	• The SQL Server startup time.
	• The current timestamp when the query is executed.


SELECT 
    @@SERVERNAME AS server_Name, 
    (SELECT COUNT(1) FROM sys.databases) AS total_databases, 
    (SELECT COUNT(1) FROM sys.databases WHERE state_desc = 'ONLINE') AS Online_databases, 
    (SELECT COUNT(1) FROM sys.databases WHERE user_access_desc = 'MULTI_USER') AS Multi_user_databases, 
    (SELECT sqlserver_start_time FROM sys.dm_os_sys_info) AS sql_startup_time, 
    GETDATE() AS query_timestamp;







